#{{philosophy}} Any overarching principle which should guide all actions; first proposed by [[Immanuel Kant]].

====Usage notes====

While there is only one categorical imperative, and thus properly no plural, the several formulations of it by Kant are sometimes referred to as "categorical imperatives". Likewise, the (e.g.) second formulation of the categorical imperative is often called "Kant's second categorical imperative".

